ğŸ› ï¸ Step-by-Step Setup Guide (Auto Table of Contents)
âœ… Step 1: Edit Your Blog Post
Go to Pages â†’ Blog â†’ Click on your post.

Click â€œEditâ€ to enter the post editor.

âœ… Step 2: Add a Code Block for the Table of Contents
Scroll to the top of your blog post.

Click â€œ+â€ â†’ Add Block â†’ Code.

Paste this code:
<div id="toc" style="margin-bottom: 20px;"></div>

<script>
  document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", function () {
    const toc = document.getElementById("toc");
    const headers = document.querySelectorAll("h2,h3,h4");
    if (!headers.length) return;

    const list = document.createElement("ul");
    headers.forEach((header, index) => {
      const id = `toc-${index}`;
      header.setAttribute("id", id);
      const item = document.createElement("li");
      item.innerHTML = `<a href="#${id}">${header.innerText}</a>`;
      list.appendChild(item);
    });
    toc.innerHTML = "<strong>Table of Contents</strong>";
    toc.appendChild(list);
  });
</script>
